<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n42066a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n42" href="#n42066a">N42 (VI.B.31)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n42all.htm#n42066a"> 66(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> devil ties 3 / knots on neck / of sleeper</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">When any one of you goeth to <mark>sleep</mark>, the <mark>Devil tieth three knots upon his neck</mark>; and saith over every knot, &ldquo;The night is long, sleep.&rdquo; <small> Stanley Lane-Poole, <a name="SLPS" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#SLPS"><cite title="source">The Speeches and Table-Talk of the Prophet Mohammad</cite></a> (1882) 150</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
